If I load a bitmap font that doesn't exist, the function `handleTaskError` from `AssetsManager` is called but the variable `toLoad` from `AssetsManager` is never decremented.
Also because cleanup occurred, `unload` will not fix this.

Example code:

```
assetsManager.load("ExampleFont.fnt", BitmapFont.class);
try {
    assetsManager.update(100);
}catch(GdxRuntimeException e) {
    // Exception is caught here but assetsManager.toLoad will remain 1 and assetsManager.loaded will remain 0.
}
```
